⚙️ 3. How you STILL reduce 40–60% cost without Spot

Now the important part.

Even without Spot, you still have big optimization areas:

⸻

💡 1. Replace overprovisioning with right-sizing (BIGGEST WIN)

Most Kubernetes clusters waste 30–50% resources.

Fix:
	•	Set proper:
	•	CPU requests
	•	Memory requests
	•	Enforce:
	•	Resource quotas
	•	Limit ranges

👉 Typical savings: 20–35%

⸻

💡 2. Use Karpenter (On-Demand only mode)

Even without Spot, Karpenter helps:
	•	Removes underutilized nodes
	•	Launches right-sized instances
	•	Eliminates static node pools

👉 Savings: 10–20%

⸻

💡 3. Optimize EKS node types (very important)

Instead of large generic instances:

Use:
	•	Compute optimized (C7i / C6i)
	•	Memory optimized only where needed

👉 Savings: 10–15%

⸻

💡 4. Reduce always-on capacity (idle waste removal)

Common issue in banks:
	•	Dev/test-like capacity running 24/7

Fix:
	•	Scale down non-production clusters
	•	Schedule scaling (business hours)

👉 Savings: 10–20%

⸻

💡 5. Storage optimization (hidden cost area)
	•	Use gp3 instead of gp2
	•	Remove unused PVCs
	•	Snapshot lifecycle policies

👉 Savings: 5–10%

⸻

💡 6. Logging control (VERY important in finance)

Logging is often 15–25% of AWS bill.

Fix:
	•	Log sampling (not full verbosity)
	•	Short retention in CloudWatch
	•	Archive to S3 with lifecycle rules

👉 Savings: 5–15%

⸻

💡 7. Network optimization
	•	Reduce NAT Gateway cost (big hidden cost)
	•	Use VPC endpoints:
	•	S3
	•	ECR
	•	CloudWatch

👉 Savings: 5–15%

⸻

